HEADWORD: Haint
<hw>Hain't</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧nt)</pr>. <def>A contraction of <sig>have
not</sig> or <sig>has not</sig>; <as>as, I <ex>hain't</ex>, he
<ex>hain't</ex>, we <ex>hain't</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq. or
illiterate speech.]</mark> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>han't</asp>.]</altsp><-- now ain't -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hair</ent>⟦br⟧
